---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { site } from '../data/site';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — Marcin Nowosielski, M.Sc. RWTH Aachen | Dentist in Poland"
  description="Marcin Nowosielski, M.Sc. RWTH Aachen — English-speaking dentist and implantologist in Opole, Poland. German university degree, premium Mikrostomart clinic, international patients."
>
  <div class="container content">
    <nav class="breadcrumbs"><a href="/">Home</a> · <span>About us</span></nav>

    <header>
      <p class="eyebrow">Your treating dentist</p>
      <h1>Marcin Nowosielski, M.Sc. RWTH Aachen</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Dentist and implantologist with a <strong>German university degree (M.Sc. RWTH Aachen)</strong>
        who speaks <strong>fluent English and German</strong>. At the premium
        <strong>Mikrostomart</strong> clinic in Opole he treats patients from the UK, Ireland,
        Germany and beyond — Western quality at Polish prices.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section>
      <h2>Why this matters</h2>
      <p>
        The most common reason patients hesitate over dental tourism is the
        <strong>language barrier</strong>. Here it disappears: Marcin Nowosielski studied in Germany
        (RWTH Aachen) and discusses your diagnosis, options, risks and costs
        <strong>personally, in English</strong> — no interpreter, no misunderstandings.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Qualifications</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>2007–2013</strong> — Dental studies, Medical University of Wrocław</li>
        <li><strong>2013</strong> — Licensed dentist, member of the Opole Medical Chamber</li>
        <li><strong>2015</strong> — Member of the Polish Endodontic Society (PTE) and ESE</li>
        <li><strong>2018–2021</strong> — <strong>Master of Science in Lasers in Dentistry, RWTH Aachen</strong> (with distinction) — one of few in Poland with this degree</li>
        <li><strong>2020+</strong> — Member of the Polish Implantology Society (PSI)</li>
        <li><strong>2024</strong> — Author of the professional book <em>„Własny gabinet"</em> (Czelej)</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Areas of focus</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Implantology</strong> — single implants, All-on-4/6, immediate placement, bone grafting, sinus lift (Straumann, Nobel Biocare)</li>
        <li><strong>Microscopic endodontics</strong> — root canal treatment under the operating microscope (ZEISS)</li>
        <li><strong>Prosthetics</strong> — crowns, bridges, fixed restoration on implants (zirconia)</li>
        <li><strong>Cosmetic dentistry</strong> — veneers, whitening, smile design</li>
        <li><strong>Laser dentistry</strong> — Er:YAG / Nd:YAG (Fotona)</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>The Mikrostomart clinic</h2>
      <p>Premium dental clinic in Opole (ul. Centralna 33a). Equipment:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>ZEISS operating microscope</li>
        <li>CBCT (3D X-ray)</li>
        <li>Intraoral scanner (digital impressions)</li>
        <li>Fotona LightWalker laser (Er:YAG + Nd:YAG)</li>
        <li>Computer-controlled anaesthesia (The Wand) — pain-free</li>
        <li>Straumann & Nobel Biocare implant systems</li>
        <li>Class B sterilisation</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Treatment philosophy</h2>
      <blockquote>
        "Precision is the key to long-lasting results. Microscope, CBCT and digital planning are
        standard here, not extras. The patient has the right to understand exactly what happens to
        their teeth, what the alternatives are and what the risks are — and to hear it in their own
        language."
      </blockquote>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>For international patients</h2>
      <p>
        We regularly care for patients from the UK, Ireland, Germany, Austria and Switzerland.
        Languages: <strong>English, German, Polish</strong>. Opole is ~1 hour from Wrocław and
        Katowice airports. <a href="/dental-tourism-poland">How it works →</a>
      </p>
    </section>

    <aside class="cta-inline">
      <h2>Free enquiry — directly with the dentist</h2>
      <p>
        Send us your X-rays or a description of your case. You'll get a free, no-obligation
        assessment and a cost estimate — personally, in English.
      </p>
      <a class="btn-primary" href={`mailto:${site.clinic.email}`}>Send enquiry →</a>
    </aside>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .content { max-width: 56rem; }
  .breadcrumbs { font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-muted); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .breadcrumbs a { text-decoration: none; }
  .content header { margin-bottom: 3rem; padding-bottom: 2rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .lead { font-size: 1.1875rem; color: var(--color-muted); }
  .eyebrow { text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-accent-dark); margin: 0 0 0.5rem; font-weight: 700; }
  section { margin: 3rem 0; }
  blockquote { margin: 1.5rem 0; padding: 1.5rem 2rem; background: var(--color-card); border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent); font-style: italic; font-size: 1.125rem; color: var(--color-primary); }
  .cta-inline { background: var(--color-primary); color: white; padding: 2.5rem 2rem; border-radius: 8px; margin-top: 4rem; }
  .cta-inline h2 { color: var(--color-accent); margin-top: 0; }
  .cta-inline p { color: #d7e8e3; }
</style>
